                            <comment id="17838785" author="knoguchi" created="Thu, 18 Apr 2024 20:12:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Uploading the patch that uses a new field introduced as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-5201&quot; title=&quot;Null handling on FLATTEN&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-5201&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-5201&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;,&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-5452&quot; title=&quot;Null handling of FLATTEN with user defined schema (as clause)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-5452&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-5452&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&#160; If number of fields are less than the expected number of fields, it will now fills the rest with null.&#160; &#160;If number of fields are more, then it would now fills up to the expected number of fields only.&#160; (pig-5453-v01.patch)&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
